  "instructions": [
    "Rinse lentils and place in a pot with water and vegetable broth.",
    "Add smoked paprika, cumin, coriander, cinnamon, crushed cardamom, and bay leaf; bring to a gentle boil.",
    "Reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, for 20 minutes until lentils soften.",
    "Stir in diced carrot and zucchini; cook for an additional 5 minutes.",
    "Add chopped gem lettuce, season with salt, and simmer for 2 minutes until wilted.",
    "Remove bay leaf, stir in lemon juice, and adjust seasoning if necessary.",
    "Ladle broth into bowls and sprinkle with fresh parsley.",
    "Serve hot as a smoky, romantic lentil broth.",
    "Pair with warm flatbread for a complete meal."
